            }
          ],
          "links": ["link", "link", "link"]
        },
        "2": {
          "id": "EC32",
          "title": "2",
          "desc":
            "Current policy is to subsidise private companies to provide a minimal bus service in rural areas, and to allow a private monopoly to decide, based on projected profit, when to upgrade an area's broadband, which is never.",
          "infograph": [
            {
              "imgsrc": "blah",
              "desc": "blahblah"
            },
            {
              "imgsrc": "blah",
              "desc": "blahblah"
            },
            {
              "imgsrc": "blah",
              "desc": "blahblah"
            },
            {
              "imgsrc": "blah",
              "desc": "blahblah"
            }
          ],
          "links": ["link", "link", "link"]
        },
        "3": {
          "id": "EC33",
          "title": "3",
          "desc":
            "So nobody in a rural area uses the buses unless it is impossible to use a car, and neither can they effectively work over the internet.",
          "infograph": [
            {
              "imgsrc": "blah",
              "desc": "blahblah"
            },
